  "body": "When using native form validation and loading a page with a form containing an input with the `required` prop set, it triggers browser validation immediately. This produces Firefox's native error highlighting. This is because Firefox appears to run validation when the DOM is used to set a value on an existing input component. \r\n\r\nThe behavior can be seen here: http://codepen.io/anon/pen/zowOzo\r\n\r\nAngular has [run into this already](https://github.com/ggershoni/angular.js/commit/cc311740c6b680c68a88c44fecd97ede1f18f831).\r\n",
